1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,360
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:04,560
At the Golden Globes

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:13,760
Jack Morgan got out of his dark blue 
Lamborghini near the Beverly Hilton.  

4
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:24,320
It was the night of the Golden Globes, and he 
was with a beautiful and famous movie star.  

5
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:37,040
He helped Guinevere Scott-Evans out of the car, 
and she held his hand hard. Guinevere trusted  

6
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:47,680
Jack, and she trusted his company, Private. 
Everyone trusted Private; it was the best.

7
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:58,080
But then Jack's oldest friend, 
Andy Cushman, called him.

8
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:06,240
Andy spoke quickly. "Jack, come 
to my house now! I need you."

9
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:14,160
"It's not a good time. What's wrong?" asked Jack.

10
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:26,800
"It's Shelby. She's dead," said Andy. 
Shelby and Andy married six months ago.

11
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:38,800
Guinevere wasn't happy, but Jack took her to 
her table. Then, he was on the road to Andy's  

12
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:48,080
house in Bluffs. He stopped near the open 
front door, took out his gun, and went in.

13
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:54,080
"Andy?" shouted Jack.

14
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:57,040
"Jack! I'm in the bedroom."

15
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:08,880
Jack went through the house, his gun in his hand. 
In the bedroom, there were clothes everywhere.  

16
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:15,600
Shelby was on the bed, with blood on her head.

17
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:20,240
"What happened?" asked Jack.

18
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:31,600
Andy was near Shelby, his head in his 
hands. "Someone shot her. Please find him!"

19
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:41,360
Jack took photos of everything in the 
room. "Did you call the police?" he asked.

20
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:47,200
"No, I wanted you here," said Andy.

21
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:51,760
"Do you have a gun?" asked Jack.

22
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,680
"No," said Andy.

23
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:08,400
"OK, you must understand. The police will want 
to talk to you. They always want it to be easy.  

24
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:20,000
They will think, 'A woman is dead - did her 
husband kill her?' But I can help," said Jack.

25
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:25,760
He called the police and waited 
for them to arrive.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

26
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,320
CHAPTER TWO

27
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,200
A young woman dies

28
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:42,160
Justine worked with Jack at 
Private. People trusted her, too.  

29
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:53,280
Tonight, she was in an expensive Italian 
restaurant. Then, the chief of police called her.

30
00:03:55,120 --> 00:04:02,160
"Another young woman is dead," 
Justine told her friend. "I must go."

31
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:13,840
In two years, eleven young women in Los 
Angeles were dead. Now, it was twelve.  

32
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:22,480
The killer always took something from 
the women - hair, a necklace, clothes.  

33
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:31,120
Then, the killer emailed the chief of police 
and told him about the women's things.  

34
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:43,680
Nobody knew where the emails came from, but 
the emails all had the same name - Steemcleena.  

35
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:52,640
The police found the women's things, 
but they couldn't find Steemcleena.  

36
00:04:53,920 --> 00:05:00,320
The police wanted Justine, and 
Private, to help them find the killer.

37
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:11,600
Emilio Cruz, from Private, stopped his Mercedes 
at the restaurant door, and Justine got in.  

38
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:17,840
"What do you know about this girl?" asked Justine.

39
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:31,920
"Her name is Connie Yu. She was sixteen and very 
intelligent," said Emilio. "She was on the ground  

40
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:40,240
behind a restaurant. There was an earring 
in her left ear. There was no right ear."

41
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:46,720
Emilio stopped in a small, dark street  

42
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:53,600
near some police cars. They walked past 
the police and spoke to the doctor.

43
00:05:55,200 --> 00:06:01,440
"We'll get an email about the ear 
in a day or two," Emilio said.

44
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:10,480
At 2 a.m., Justine and Emilio 
were at Private's offices.  

45
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:16,160
They talked to Sci, Private's forensic expert.  

46
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:26,720
"We have the woman's bag and cell phone," 
said Justine. "Can you look for DNA on them?"

47
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:34,720
"Of course," said Sci. "I can 
work all night on it."
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

48
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,200
CHAPTER THREE

49
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,040
At Private

50
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:53,280
The next morning, Justine, Emilio, Sci, and 
Mo-bot, the computer expert, were in the office.

51
00:06:54,720 --> 00:07:05,040
Jack opened his laptop and showed them the photos 
from Andy's bedroom. "Look at these," he said.  

52
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:10,320
"I can't see anything important. Can you?"

53
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:17,680
"Did the killer take anything 
from the house?" asked Justine.

54
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:23,360
"No, he took nothing," said Jack.

55
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:31,680
"And were Andy and Shelby 
happy together?" asked Emilio.

56
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:36,720
"Yes," said Jack. "Very happy."

57
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:48,640
"OK," said Justine. "This killer is a 
professional. But why did he kill Shelby?"

58
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:54,000
"The police always like easy answers.  

59
00:07:54,960 --> 00:08:03,920
They will think one thing: Andy killed 
her," said Emilio. "Did Andy kill her?"

60
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:13,760
"No, he didn't," said Jack. "I 
know Andy well. He loved Shelby."

61
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,880
"What next?" asked Mo-bot.

62
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:23,280
"We look at Andy and Shelby,"  

63
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:31,680
said Jack. "We talk to their friends 
and to people they work with. Let's go."

64
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:39,840
"Wait!" said Justine. "I have 
some news on the young woman.  

65
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:51,200
We have her bag. Sci couldn't find any 
new DNA, but Mo-bot looked at her phone."

66
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:59,920
"I looked at the text messages," 
said Mo-bot. "There were hundreds,  

67
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:08,160
from twenty or thirty people. I looked 
at the numbers, and they are all  

68
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:18,960
friends or family. But there is one strange 
message - I can't get the number for it. Look!"

69
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:24,160
A text message came up on the wall.
 
 

70
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:37,920
Connie. It's Linda. My mom took my phone. 
I must talk to you. Can we meet? Please!  

71
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:47,040
Behind the restaurant. At 
8.30 p.m. Don't tell anyone.
 
 

72
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:56,560
"I talked to Linda," said Mo-bot. 
"Her mother didn't take her phone.  

73
00:09:57,760 --> 00:10:08,000
Linda didn't send that message. The killer got 
into Connie's phone and found all her friends.  

74
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:14,080
Then, he sent her that message from his phone."

75
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:25,200
"But we can't find the number of the killer's 
phone," said Sci. "It isn't possible."

76
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:31,840
"Who is Steemcleena?" asked Jack.

77
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:46,560
Rudolph Crocker left his office at 7 p.m. and 
went for a drink. At 9 p.m., he was at home and  

78
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:57,920
ready for a run. He ran out to Marina del Rey and 
thought about Connie Yu. That was a great evening.

79
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:04,000
There was nobody near him. He stopped near a boat  

80
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:13,840
and put something on it. Then, he went home 
and sent an email to the Chief of Police.

81
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:23,600
You can find Connie Yu's ear on a boat in 
Marina del Rey. Steemcleena.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

82
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,080
CHAPTER FOUR

83
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,560
Another young woman

84
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:38,160
Jason Pilser got a text message at work at 3 p.m.

85
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:48,720
Scylla, your big night is 
Saturday. Be ready. Steemcleena.

86
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:57,680
"Scylla" was Jason's computer 
name. At 6 p.m., he left his office  

87
00:11:58,240 --> 00:12:08,240
and drove to a store. He bought some gloves and 
some electric cable. He didn't pay with a card,  

88
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:16,240
and he looked down at the ground. He didn't 
want the cameras in the store to see him.

89
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:25,520
The big night was in three days. He 
was ready to kill his first woman.

90
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:34,960
"I'm going for a walk!" Marguerite 
Esperanza shouted to her grandmother.  

91
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:44,160
It was Saturday evening. Marguerite walked 
out the house and on to Rowena Avenue.  

92
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,840
A text message came on to her phone.

93
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:54,000
Hi Marg. It's Lamar. Where are you?

94
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,600
She read it and answered.

95
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,960
I'm on Rowena.

96
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:08,000
Lamar was a really nice boy. Marguerite liked him.

97
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:15,360
Do you want to get a pizza? asked Lamar.

98
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:19,840
OK, Marguerite answered.

99
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,680
Marguerite called her grandmother.  

100
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:34,160
"I'm getting a pizza with Lamar," she said. 
"And he'll walk home with me. Is that OK?"

101
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:43,840
The black van was near Rowena 
Avenue. The driver was Steemcleena.  

102
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:48,880
Scylla and Morbid were in the back of the van.

103
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:57,680
"She's out of her house," said 
Morbid. He gave the laptop to Scylla.

104
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:05,440
Scylla wrote a message: Hi Marg. It's Lamar...

105
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:14,480
Marguerite answered. Scylla 
wrote another message. The van  

106
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:22,800
stopped near the pizza restaurant and waited. 
Then, they saw Marguerite in the street.

107
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:35,200
"Go!" shouted Morbid. Scylla got out of the 
van. He pulled a bag over Marguerite's head  

108
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:45,600
from behind, and he and Morbid threw her 
into the van. Steemcleena drove away quickly.

109
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:51,120
"Help!" shouted Marguerite.

110
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:59,840
"Be quiet!" shouted Morbid. 
"Maybe you can win the game."

111
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:06,160
"Win?" asked Marguerite. "What do you mean?"

112
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:19,360
Steemcleena stopped the van in a park, with nobody 
near. Morbid and Steemcleena were behind Scylla.  

113
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,800
This was Scylla's game.

114
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:31,360
Marguerite got out of the van quickly, 
and she pulled the bag off her head.  

115
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:41,920
She couldn't run away; Steemcleena and Morbid 
could stop her. But she was tall and strong,  

116
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:49,840
and ready for Scylla. Her hand 
flew out and hit him on the nose.

117
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:58,960
There was blood on Scylla's face 
now, and he was angry. He ran at her,  

118
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:08,000
but she kicked him hard in the 
stomach. And then she kicked him again.

119
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:18,000
Steemcleena looked at Morbid. "She's too 
good for Scylla," he said. He took out a gun  

120
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:26,240
and shot Marguerite in the head. 
Then, Scylla put on the gloves  

121
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:35,840
and put the cable around the dead woman's neck. 
He took her shoes and put them in the van.

122
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:49,840
"That wasn't good," said Steemcleena to Scylla. 
"But maybe you'll win the next game."
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

123
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:51,840
CHAPTER FIVE

124
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,800
Scylla's next game

125
00:16:57,040 --> 00:17:04,320
Justine met Police Lieutenant Nora 
Cronin in the park at 4 a.m. on Sunday.  

126
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:12,720
"The Chief of Police is here," said 
Nora. "He wants to talk to you."

127
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:23,120
The Chief was with three police officers near 
Marguerite's body. Justine walked up to him.

128
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:34,960
"It's good to see you," he said. "We need 
your help. Thirteen women are dead. And look!  

129
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:42,400
Somebody shot her dead - so why 
is there cable around her neck?"

130
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:51,360
"It's very strange," said Justine. 
"And where's her handbag?"

131
00:17:53,120 --> 00:18:02,800
"There's no handbag," said the Chief, 
"and no shoes. I'm waiting for the email."

132
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:13,840
On Sunday evening, Scylla was on the terrace of 
his apartment, at the top of a tall building.  

133
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:24,560
The city was beautiful at night, but he didn't 
look at it. His face and body were black and blue.  

134
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:34,720
"That girl was strong," he thought. Then, 
he read the message from Morbid again.

135
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:42,560
You weren't good yesterday, 
Scylla. Steemcleena isn't happy.  

136
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:53,120
But you can play again tonight. We have 
someone for you. Be ready at 7 p.m.

137
00:18:55,600 --> 00:19:02,560
Morbid and Steemcleena were at the 
door now, and Scylla went to open it.

138
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:07,520
"How's the nose?" asked Morbid.

139
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:13,760
OK, said Scylla. "Do you want a drink?"

140
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:24,480
"No," said Steemcleena. "Let's go on the 
terrace. I want to show you something."

141
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:35,680
The three men walked on to the terrace and 
looked down at the city. Then, Steemcleena  

142
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:48,400
turned to Scylla. "You think you can play again?" 
he asked. "You can. But you're playing with us."

143
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:53,200
Steemcleena took Scylla's legs,  

144
00:19:53,920 --> 00:20:00,160
and Morbid took his arms, and they 
threw him over the terrace wall.

145
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:10,240
Justine and Jack were at Private with 
Mo-bot. They talked about Marguerite.

146
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:15,760
"The killer sent an email," said Justine,  

147
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:25,120
"and we found her shoes. Sci is looking 
at them now, but they're probably clean."

148
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:38,000
"The killer is using a van to look for the young 
women, I think," said Mo-bot. "He has a laptop  

149
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:49,360
and a radio in the van, and he can send messages 
to the women's cell phones. He can stop messages  

150
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:59,520
to their phones from other people, too. And maybe 
he can find them in the street from their phones."

151
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:04,480
"Is that possible?" asked Jack.

152
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:12,160
"I don't know. I'll ask 
Sci about it," said Mo-bot.  

153
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:17,920
"His friend Kit-Kat knows about cell phones."

154
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:22,800
"I remembered something important,"  

155
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:33,440
said Justine. "Someone killed a woman about 
five years ago in the same street as Connie Yu.  

156
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:44,000
Her name was Wendy Borman. The killer 
took her phone. And her necklace."

157
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:47,040
"Five years ago!" said Jack.  

158
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:57,840
"Maybe it's not thirteen women. Maybe it's 
more! We have work to do!"
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

159
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,560
CHAPTER SIX

160
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:04,240
An angry husband can kill

161
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:13,280
On Monday morning, Andy was at Private. 
Jack had something to tell him.

162
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:22,080
"I can't sleep," Andy said. "I 
think about Shelby all the time."

163
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:34,880
"Andy," said Jack. "We talked to a lot of people 
about Shelby. She had a lot of friends - you know  

164
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:47,120
that. And we found one very good friend. The movie 
star Bob Santangelo. She saw him every week."

165
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:54,480
"That's not true!" shouted Andy. "She loved me."

166
00:22:56,160 --> 00:23:05,360
"Maybe she loved you," said Jack. "But she 
loved Santangelo, too. Did you know that?"

167
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:11,440
"No, I didn't!" shouted Andy. "It's not true!"

168
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:19,040
Andy left. Jack and Sci talked about Santangelo.

169
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:26,400
"Did Andy know about Santangelo?" asked Sci.

170
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:30,800
"I don't know," said Jack.

171
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:37,040
"An angry husband can kill, you know," said Sci.

172
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:49,840
"I know, Sci," said Jack. "But Andy's a good 
man, and he's my friend. He didn't kill Shelby."

173
00:23:51,520 --> 00:24:04,000
"I understand. You don't want to hear 
it," said Sci. "But maybe he did."

174
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:08,960
Justine was at the police station 
with Lieutenant Nora Cronin.

175
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:20,640
"I looked on the internet," said Justine, 
"but can you tell me more about Wendy Borman?"

176
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:32,160
"One thing isn't on the internet," said Nora. "An 
eleven-year-old girl called Christine Castiglia  

177
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:42,800
saw something. She and her mother were in a 
coffee shop on Melrose Avenue. Christine saw two  

178
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:52,240
boys push Wendy into a van. Her mother didn't 
see anything, and Christine didn't see a lot.  

179
00:24:53,360 --> 00:25:01,440
The boys were white. One had a long nose 
and big ears; the other had long hair."

180
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:14,080
"But Christine is sixteen now," said Justine. 
"We need to talk to her again."
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

181
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:15,040
CHAPTER SEVEN

182
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:18,320
Help from Sci's friends

183
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:24,720
Sci lived in an apartment with a lot of computers.  

184
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:33,680
On Monday evening, he sat at a computer 
and talked to his friend Kit-Kat in Sweden.

185
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:41,840
"You asked about cell phones," 
said Kit-Kat. "I can help.  

186
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:53,680
Someone in the United States of America has a new 
program. It can find a phone and get inside it.  

187
00:25:54,800 --> 00:26:02,640
Then, it can send messages from the 
phone. And nobody knows it is happening."

188
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:12,320
"That's great, Kit-Kat," said Sci. 
"Do you know who made this program?"

189
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:19,280
"His name is Morbid. He's American, I think."

190
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:23,840
"Thanks, Kit-Kat. You're wonderful!"

191
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:38,080
Then, Sci sent a message to his friend Darren, who 
was in India. Darren played games on computers.

192
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:41,760
Do you know a player called Morbid?

193
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:51,840
Yes. I saw a message from a player 
called Scylla about Morbid. On Saturday.

194
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,320
What did he say?

195
00:26:55,680 --> 00:27:05,520
He said: "I'm playing a new game with Morbid." 
Then, there was a message from Morbid the next  

196
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:19,920
day. "Scylla can fly. He flew off his terrace. 
Flying is easy, but the streets are hard."

197
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:28,640
Sci looked on the internet. On Sunday, 
a man fell off a terrace in Los Angeles  

198
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:38,160
and died. His name was Jason Pilser. 
"Was that Scylla?" Sci thought.

199
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:45,760
Sci met Jack in a coffee shop 
early on Tuesday morning.

200
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:57,200
"Jack, I have some news. Lots of people like 
playing games on the internet. In some of these  

201
00:27:57,200 --> 00:28:07,920
games, you kill people, but you're playing - 
it's a game. I think some men in Los Angeles  

202
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:18,640
are playing a game, but they are really killing 
people. Not on the computer, but on the streets."

203
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:24,080
