281
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:28,240
Justine had yearbooks for three years from 
Gateway school with photos of all the students.  

282
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:36,800
She put them on the table. "Can you look 
at these? Maybe one of the boys is there."

283
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:46,480
Christine turned the pages of the yearbooks. 
She stopped and looked at a photo of a group  

284
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:57,600
of boys. "That's him!" she said. She showed 
Justine. The boy had a long nose and big ears.

285
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:05,040
Justine looked at the name under 
the photo. Rudolph Crocker.

286
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:09,440
"Great job, Christine!" she said.

287
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:20,560
She opened her laptop and looked for Rudolph 
Crocker. There were two in Los Angeles. The first  

288
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:28,880
was sixty-six years old. The second worked 
for a small company on Wilshire Boulevard.  

289
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:36,080
And there was a photo of him. It 
was the boy, five years older.

290
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:41,840
Now, Justine needed his DNA.

291
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:46,640
Justine went to see Nora 
Cronin at the police station.  

292
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:55,840
"We have DNA from Wendy Borman's clothes," 
